Package: LibeRtAD
Type: Package
Title: C++ Automatic Differentiation Engine for LibeR
Version: 0.7.5
Authors@R: person("Sven C.", "van Dijkman",
    email = "svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Sven C. van Dijkman [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Sven C. van Dijkman <svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: Compiles a restricted R-like mathematical model language to a
    serializable intermediate representation and evaluates persistent CppAD
    tapes using the bundled CppAD 20260000.0 and Eigen 5.0.1 headers. Dynamic parameters allow
    non-differentiated data to change without retaping, and optimized graph
    caches reconstruct tapes with exact source-provenance checks. A small R6
    wrapper owns external pointers while numerical evaluation, gradients,
    dense or sparse Jacobians, Hessians, and guarded tensor and Smolyak sparse
    Gauss-Hermite quadrature grids execute in C++.
    Includes reproducible automatic-differentiation benchmarks and a local
    React workbench that can also launch the paired LibeRation and NONMEM
    validation harness from a LibeR source checkout.
